data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_3613384\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 09, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104gvp1665702611605.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gvp1665702611605.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gvp1665702611605.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"gvp1665702611605\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Vertical Alignment (\n                              Valign)\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">This property determines the vertical alignment of data (text or image) in the widget, entity, area frame, or window.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gvp1665702611605__p_d99791e1_d99792e1_d99793e1\">\n         \n                                valign\n                                <code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">\"</code>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">Top</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">Center</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">Bottom</code>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">\"</code>\n</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"gvp1665702611605__table_d11591e1_d11592e1_d11593e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"gvp1665702611605__table_d11591e1_d11592e1_d11593e1__entry__1\">\n Value\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"gvp1665702611605__table_d11591e1_d11592e1_d11593e1__entry__2\">\n Description\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gvp1665702611605__table_d11591e1_d11592e1_d11593e1__entry__1\">\n (default)\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gvp1665702611605__table_d11591e1_d11592e1_d11593e1__entry__2\">Data is positioned according to the\n                        <span class=\"ph filepath\">.ini</span> file. If no entry is specified, the system\n                     defaults are used: <code class=\"ph codeph\">Center</code> for Pictures and Command buttons. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gvp1665702611605__table_d11591e1_d11592e1_d11593e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">Top</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gvp1665702611605__table_d11591e1_d11592e1_d11593e1__entry__2\">\n Data is positioned at the top of the widget. Default for Hyperlink widget.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gvp1665702611605__table_d11591e1_d11592e1_d11593e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">Center</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gvp1665702611605__table_d11591e1_d11592e1_d11593e1__entry__2\">Data is positioned in the center of the widget.\n                     Default for Picture and CommandButton widgets. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gvp1665702611605__table_d11591e1_d11592e1_d11593e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">Bottom</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gvp1665702611605__table_d11591e1_d11592e1_d11593e1__entry__2\">\n Data is positioned at the bottom of the widget.\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gvp1665702611605__section_uhc_wdl_swb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d219902e162\">Usage</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"gvp1665702611605__table_d11594e1_d11595e1_d11596e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Dynamic? </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Yes </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Supported in Grid? </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Yes for Grid, Command Button, and Picture\n                     </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Dependencies: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> None </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gvp1665702611605__section_zjq_xdl_swb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d219902e208\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gvp1665702611605__p_d99800e1_d99801e1_d99802e1\">For command buttons, this property only works if the\n               <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Representation</span> property is set to\n            <code class=\"ph codeph\">Uniface</code>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gvp1665702611605__p_d99803e1_d99804e1_d99805e1\">For grid widgets, this property applies to cells in\n            the grid.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gvp1665702611605__section_oys_zdl_swb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d219902e226\">Example: Setting in ProcScript</h2>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"gvp1665702611605__pre_w1m_b2l_swb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">$fieldproperties(FLD1) = \"valign=bottom\"</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gvp1665702611605__section_l2q_b2l_swb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d219902e236\">Applies To</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"gvp1665702611605__ul_hyg_f2l_swb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gvp1665702611605__li_d40316e1_d40317e1_d40318e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jrc1665702631553.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jrc1665702631553.html\" title=\"The CommandButton is a logical widget that enables a user to initiate an action by clicking the button.\">CommandButton</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gvp1665702611605__li_d40319e1_d40320e1_d40321e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"clg1695282025414.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/clg1695282025414.html\" title=\"The egrid widget displays data in a tabular format, in which the rows are occurrences of an entity and the columns are fields. It is an entity-level widget that is only applicable to form components.\">egrid (Grid)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gvp1665702611605__li_d40322e1_d40323e1_d40324e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"dzy1665702618507.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dzy1665702618507.html\" title=\"This property determines whether the widget behaves as a hyperlink (True; default) or a dynamic label False.\">Hyperlink</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gvp1665702611605__li_d40325e1_d40326e1_d40327e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rgn1665702634165.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rgn1665702634165.html\" title=\"Image to use as the background image on the map widget.\">Image Name</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gvp1665702611605__li_d40328e1_d40329e1_d40330e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"iic1718342502908.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/iic1718342502908.html\" title=\"The udefentity widget is the default widget for entities in form components. It is a multi-occurrence list, with a minimum of one occurrence, in which fields can be freely arranged. Uniface provides a default logical widget called DefEntity that is mapped to this widget.\">udefentity (Default Entity Widget )</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gvp1665702611605__li_d40331e1_d40332e1_d40333e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ujj1665702610581.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ujj1665702610581.html\" title=\"Area frames are objects that can be used to group or separate the contents of a Form component.\">Area Frames and Lines</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"gvp1665702611605__ul_syg_f2l_swb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gvp1665702611605__li_d40334e1_d40335e1_d40336e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"scc1665702611448.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/scc1665702611448.html\" title=\"Image used as background for the application window, form, or entity. This property can be set in ProcScript.\">Background Image (BackImage)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gvp1665702611605__li_d40337e1_d40338e1_d40339e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ula1665702613468.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ula1665702613468.html\" title=\"An Entity defines a logical data aggregation. It usually represents a relational database table, but it is possible to define non-database entities for transient data, reusable user interface controls, or other application structures.\">Entities</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/btj1665702631955.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Representation</a><p>This property determines the appearance of the command button when running on the Microsoft Windows operating system (XP and later versions). One of Windows (default), Uniface, or Header.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3613384\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3613384\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Vertical Alignment ( Valign) Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 09, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Vertical Alignment ( Valign) This property determines the vertical alignment of data (text or image) in the widget, entity, area frame, or window. valign = \" Top | Center | Bottom \" Value Description (default) Data is positioned according to the .ini file. If no entry is specified, the system defaults are used: Center for Pictures and Command buttons. Top Data is positioned at the top of the widget. Default for Hyperlink widget. Center Data is positioned in the center of the widget. Default for Picture and CommandButton widgets. Bottom Data is positioned at the bottom of the widget. Usage Dynamic? Yes Supported in Grid? Yes for Grid, Command Button, and Picture Dependencies: None Description For command buttons, this property only works if the Representation property is set to Uniface . For grid widgets, this property applies to cells in the grid. Example: Setting in ProcScript $fieldproperties(FLD1) = \"valign=bottom\" Copy Applies To CommandButton egrid (Grid) Hyperlink Image Name udefentity (Default Entity Widget ) Area Frames and Lines Background Image (BackImage) Entities Related Links Representation This property determines the appearance of the command button when running on the Microsoft Windows operating system (XP and later versions). One of Windows (default), Uniface, or Header. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}